---
import Layout from "../../components/Layout.astro";
import Breadcrumbs from "../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro";
---

<Layout title="News" description="Pi World Ranking List news and migration notes." path="/news/">
  <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: "News" }]} />
  <section class="content narrow">
    <h1>News</h1>
    <h2>Migration Note</h2>
    <p>
      This repository is a static rebuild of the public site. The archived live site announced that
      the Pi World Ranking List was on hold; that status is preserved here until Ari reviews and
      updates the public process.
    </p>

    <h2>Announcement From The Archived Site</h2>
    <p>
      The old site announced plans for a book about members of the Pi World Ranking List and invited
      interested members to contact the maintainer.
    </p>

    <h2>The Pi World Ranking List Is Back Online</h2>
    <p>
      The old news page noted that the lists were simplified to make updates easier and that photos
      would usually no longer be published. It also stated that age classifications such as youngest
      or oldest person on the list would no longer be maintained.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
